11/10/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Turkey's Chief General Staff Gen Hilmi Ozkok met his Romanian counterpart, Gen Mihail Popescu, on Thursday (10 October). The two discussed the progress of military reforms and Romania's bid for NATO membership. They also pledged that their countries would continue to contribute to the stability and security of Southeast Europe. Ozkok arrived in Romania after spending two days in Bulgaria.
Meanwhile, the Chief of Staff of Bulgaria's naval forces, Vice Adm Neyko Atanasov, has presented plans to build six new corvettes to join Bulgaria's fleet. The ships would be built completely in line with NATO standards, at a cost of 140m euros apiece. (Rompres, BTA, BBC - 10/10/02)
